  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<h3>Defensive 1</h3>\n<p>When you make your first attack on your turn with a weapon with the defensive property, you can choose to suffer a penalty to attack and damage rolls with that weapon up to the defensive number. If you do so, you gain the same bonus to AC. These effects last until the start of your next turn, as long as you're holding the weapon.</p>\n<h3>Disguised</h3>\n<p>You have advantage on Charisma (Deception) checks made to hide the nature of a weapon with this property.</p>\n<h3>Returning </h3>\n<p>When you throw a weapon with this property, it automatically returns to your hand after the attack is complete, whether you hit or miss.</p>\n<h3>Thrown (range 30/90)</h3>\n<p>A weapon that can be used to make a ranged attack has this property. The range lists two numbers. The first is the weapon's normal range in feet, and the second indicates the weapon's long range. When attacking a target beyond normal range, you have disadvantage on the attack roll. You can't attack a target beyond the weapon's long range.</p>",
